{"type":"message","id":"2bd6be57","parentId":"657abbd3","timestamp":"2026-03-31T02:30:50.908Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"☀️ 𝐆𝐨𝐨𝐝 𝐌𝐨𝐫𝐧𝐢𝐧𝐠, 𝐍𝐫𝐞𝐱𝐲𝐚! ☀️\nTuesday, March 31st — the last day of March! 🌸\n\nHope you all slept like royalty. Here's some positivity to kick off your day 👇\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n📰 𝐆𝐨𝐨𝐝 𝐍𝐞𝐰𝐬\n\n🔬 **New immunotherapy giving hope for advanced prostate cancer** — VIR-5500 is showing significant PSA reduction and even tumor shrinkage in early studies. Science keeps pushing boundaries.\n\n🌬️ **China successfully generates electricity from high-altitude winds** — A 60-meter helium-filled system at 2,000 meters tapped into stronger, more consistent winds. Clean energy just got more creative.\n\n🐔 **Norway phasing out \"turbo chickens\" by 2027** — Replacing fast-growing breeds with more animal-friendly ones. A historic win for animal welfare advocates worldwide.\n\n🧪 **Liquid biopsy improving childhood cancer diagnosis in Africa** — A new test allows faster, more precise detection of aggressive Burkitt lymphoma in kids. Faster diagnosis = faster treatment.\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n🧠 𝐁𝐫𝐚𝐢𝐧 𝐓𝐞𝐚𝐬𝐞𝐫\n\n\"If you could relive one day of your life exactly as it happened — not change anything, just *experience* it again — would you? And does the answer tell you more about what you value, or what you regret?\"\n\nDrop your answers below ⬇️💬\n\nHave a brilliant Tuesday, everyone! 💛⚡"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774924250908}}
